sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1973007
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: nahR (Pseudomonas putida, see BBa_K1031610) is expressed under the constitutive Pr promoter. It encodes a regulatory protein that activates the Psal promoter (see BBa_J61051) in the presence of salicylate. lapG (see BBa_K1973000) is expressed from the Psal promoter in the presence of this molecule. nasF (see BBa_K1973001) is an attenuator of transcription elongation (terminator) from Klebsiella pneumoniae that decreases the basal expression from the Psal promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Alvaro Escobar Doncel
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We digested BBa_K1973000 as a vector (EcoRI and XbaI) and BBa_K1973005 as an insert (EcoRI and SpeI), and then we ligate them.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Laura Claret Fern??ndez
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It was obtained by PCR from a plasmid containing this sequence. The PCR primers added the prefix and suffix needed.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We had included the RBS BBa_B0034 in the PCR primers, as well as the scar it should have appeared in the cloning of the DNA piece.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1973001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: nasF is an attenuator of transcription elongation (terminator) from Klebsiella pneumoniae that decreases the basal expression from the Psal promoter. The nasR protein disrupts the terminator structure and allows the expression again, providing an useful tool for tight ON/OFF expression systems.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Laura Claret Fern??ndez
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It was obtained by PCR from a plasmid containing its sequence.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1973000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Codifies the LapG protein from Pseudomonas putida KT2442, a periplasmic protease that participates in the biofilm dispersion process by cleaving adhesion proteins such as LapA.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Laura Claret Fern??ndez
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Obtained by PCR from the genome of Pseudomonas putida KT2442.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We have inlcuded the sequence corresponding to RBS BBa_B0034 with the PCR primers used for its amplification, as well as the scar it should have been produced by the clonning of both parts
